h-based operators\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:66:- coarse operators derived from fine operators and transfer maps\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:70:- metric-aware and standard for diffusion / wave equations on surfaces\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:73:- gives a principled path to Galerkin coarse operators\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:91:This is the default the later wave engine should treat as scientifically\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:98:- coarse operator by Galerkin projection from the fine operator\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:111:- normalized coarse operator `A_c = M_c^{-1/2} K_c M_c^{-1/2}`\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:114:fine surface operator instead of from an unrelated patch-edge heuristic.\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:118:`meshing.operator_assembly` is the versioned user-facing config block that\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:119:drives fine-operator assembly. The current schema version is\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:120:`operator_assembly.v1`.\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:148:Identity anisotropy is required to reproduce the isotropic operator within an\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:149:absolute operator tolerance of `1e-10`, and the tests enforce that bound.\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:158:  ablations, and downstream solver plumbing; it is not a license to change\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:165:- only the diagonal tangent-basis model is supported in `operator_assembly.v1`\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:169:- anisotropy is for declared directional conductivity or wave-speed modifiers,\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:174:Fallback is allowed when the default operator cannot be serialized safely or has\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:187:3. a regression fixture needs a deterministic structural operator without the\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:191:per-root `operator_bundle.discretization_family`, `mass_treatment`,\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:196:The later wave engine inherits these expectations:\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:202:- undamped wave propagation should not gain energy from the spatial operator\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:203:- any damping operator must be positive semidefinite and separate from the\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:204:  conservative spatial operator\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:213:- stiffness operators are symmetric\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:214:- mass operators are positive diagonal after lumping\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:215:- the effective generalized operator is positive semidefinite\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:220:- coarse operators and transfer maps should be interpreted in the same inner\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:221:  product as the fine operator\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:225:`operator_bundle.v2` serializes:\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:227:- a dedicated fine operator archive with cotangent stiffness, lumped mass,\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:228:  symmetric mass-normalized operator form, and explicit supporting geometry\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:230:- anisotropy coefficients needed to reproduce the fine operator:\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:233:- a dedicated coarse operator archive with patch mass, Galerkin stiffness, the\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:234:  normalized coarse operator, and patch-local supporting arrays\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:235:- an explicit transfer-operator archive with physical-field restriction /\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:236:  prolongation, normalized-state transfer operators, and quality metrics\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:237:- an operator metadata sidecar that records the realized discretization,\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:238:  weighting scheme, frame convention, versioned `operator_assembly` config,\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
